President Trump announced that he and the First Lady will be traveling to Las Vegas to pay their respects and offer condolences to the victims of the recent shooting. He also expressed his love for the people of the country and gratitude for the support received in Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands. Governor Kenneth Mapp thanked the President and his team for their help in rebuilding the Virgin Islands after the hurricanes. Both governors expressed their support for Puerto Rico and their willingness to assist.